again, it’s been the same ethos since i started. keep the doors open that i walk thru as it’s the logic i believe in the most. nothing is as reassuring as this slideshow above. i’m so particular that it’s vital there’s physical artifacts of wide sweeping ideas or it doesn’t count in my book. 

please find the work of the multitude of artists i value from my specific corner of the world. each given free reign to bounce ideas off the @louisvuitton seat i sit at. follow them and dive into their premise. to be continued... #louis200

node.text: @off____white™ logic® feat. leather goods

this @feliciathegoat interview on @hot97 is something different. i woke up wanting to teach a dual lecture at Howard & Harvard University at the exact same time, and if i do it, this would be the first required text to study. it’s scary good. ultra high intellect. nuanced AF and specific at the same time. 

watch the whole thing. even me taking a clip out does a disservice to the full train of thought. critical thinking always wins. critical thinking in our space of rap-fashion-art-culture is, well… mind bending. ~ if you look for the youtube link you’ll find it.
